gs":["English (of Norman origin): occupational name for a watchman, either in a town or castle, from Anglo-Norman French <i>waite</i> ‘watchman, member of the watch’ (of ancient Germanic origin; compare   Wachter  ). In the Middle Ages the town waits typically combined the functions of watchmen and musicians through being trumpeters or pipers. There may also have been some late confusion with   White   or   Wheat  ."]}]},{"name":"Ralph","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From a Norman French name, <i>Raulf</i>, a contracted form of the Germanic personal name <i>Radulf</i>, derived from <i>rād</i> ‘counsel’ + <i>wulf</i> ‘wolf’. The spelling with <i>-ph</i> is due to classical influence in the 18th century."],"variants":[{"name":"Ralf","meanings":["From a Norman French name, <i>Raulf</i>, a contracted form of the Germanic personal name <i>Radulf</i>, derived from <i>rād</i> ‘counsel’ + <i>wulf</i> ‘wolf’. The spelling with <i>-ph</i> is due to classical influence in the 18th century."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Sir Ralph Wake was born in 1252, in Thetford, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 2 daughters."},"et":{"1252–":"1252–Surnud","1268–1351":"1268–1351","1270–Female":"1270–Surnud","1252–Male":"1252–Surnud","1268":"1268","1252":"1252","1351":"1351","1270":"1270","Thetford, Norfolk, England":"Thetford, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1252–":"1252–Kuollut","1268–1351":"1268–1351","1270–Female":"1270–Kuollut","1252–Male":"1252–Kuollut","1268":"1268","1252":"1252","1351":"1351","1270":"1270","Thetford, Norfolk, England":"Thetford, Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1252–":"1252–Décédé","1268–1351":"1268–1351","1270–Female":"1270–Décédée","1252–Male":"1252–Décédé","1268":"1268","1252":"1252","1351":"1351","1270":"1270","Thetford, Norfolk, England":"Thetford, Norfolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Sir Ralph Wake est né en 1252, à Thetford